$ Shell command: fdisk
@ fdisk


`fdisk` can create and manipulate → hardware/harddisk/partition-table[partition tables].

Apparently, fdisk only manages MS-DOS partition layouts (→ hardware/harddisk/MBR[MBR's]). In order to manipulate → hardware/harddisk/GPT[GPT's] (apparently necessary harddisks > 2TB), use → Linux/shell/commands/gdisk (the GPT fdisk).

sa:

  → Linux/shell/commands/gdisk, → Linux/shell/commands/sgdisk

  → Linux/shell/commands/index[Shell commands]
